Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Remove all the packaging and pop the @Irish Pork Ribs{500%grams} into an #oven dish{}. Cover with #foil{} and cook in the #oven{} for ~{25-30%minutes}.

Meanwhile, combine @Hoisin Sauce{2%sachets} and @Sweet Chilli Sauce{1%sachet} in a #small bowl{}.

In the last ~{5%minutes} of cooking time, remove the foil from the oven dish.

Add the sauce and pop back in the oven uncovered, ~{5%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Ensure the ribs are piping hot throughout.

Pour @Water{300%ml}(cold, salted) into a #medium pot{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the @Jasmine Rice{150%grams} and bring to the boil.

Once boiling, lower the heat to medium, cover with the lid and cook for ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, remove the #pot{} from the heat.

Keep covered for another ~{12%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Trim and cut the @Green Beans{150%grams} into thirds.

Peel and grate the @Garlic{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Trim and thinly slice the @Scallion{2}.

Halve, deseed and thinly slice the @Chilli{1}.

Meanwhile, place a pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}.

Once hot, add the green beans.

Cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add garlic, @Honey{1%sachet} and half the chilli.

Cook, stirring occasionally, ~{2-3%minutes}. Season with @Salt{to taste} and @Pepper{to taste}.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{}.

Stir in half the scallions and @Apple Cider Vinegar{1%sachet} to taste.

Divide rice, veg and ribs between plates.

Sprinkle @Peanuts{20%grams} over the veg.

Scatter the remaining chilli and scallion over the ribs.